      {
        "header": "Narrative and Justification",
        "description": null,
        "fields": [
          {
            "field_id": "microsoft_forms:01:r5d9b7f157ad24b1498f9bedef37b3989:e91b82ff34b3",
            "label": "Please Provide a Description of Your Request:",
            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "text",
            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "This programmatic request seeks $9 billion for NASA's Science Mission Directorate (SMD) to restore stability to the nation's space science enterprise following recent funding volatility. This investment supports critical decadal priorities and sustains high-tech research at institutions like the University of Nebraska-Lincoln, which has received over $1.7 million in recent NASA grants for projects ranging from satellite-based irrigation scheduling to drought tracking and advanced laser sterilization for space hardware. Restoring SMD funding ensures the U.S. remains the global leader in space exploration while directly benefiting Nebraska's agricultural and technological workforce.",
            "rationale": "The draft value combines the specific $9B programmatic ask with local evidence of NASA's impact in NE-1, specifically citing the Board of Regents of the University of Nebraska's research in satellite irrigation and drought monitoring. It incorporates advocacy themes of national leadership and workforce stability as requested in the framing guide.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "field_id": "microsoft_forms:01:rab877e8fe6e84f13b3138201eeebcd25:3be866cf1c0c",
            "label": "If the Request is for Funding, Why is this Funding a Good Use of Taxpayer Funds?",
            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": false,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* NASA Science generates approximately $3 for every $1 invested, strengthening the industrial base and skilled innovation workforce.\n* Space science is a core public responsibility under Title 51 of the U.S. Code, driving discovery and national prestige no private entity can replicate.\n* These investments provide practical data for weather forecasting, agricultural management, and planetary defense.",
            "rationale": "Drawn from the economic and public responsibility talking points in the advocacy context.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "field_id": "microsoft_forms:01:rd278700559d34f509689c397336ec6a1:951b4e118d74",
            "label": "Please Provide a Brief Justification for the Request (Why should the funding level be changed/why is this language necessary?): ",
            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* Funding at $9 billion is essential to restore workforce stability and counteract aggressive space science expansion by China.\n* Stable funding protects the decades of bipartisan investment that established American leadership in space exploration.\n* This level enables NASA to execute the National Academies' decadal survey priorities, which represent the vetted consensus of the scientific community.",
            "rationale": "Utilizes the workforce stability and competition with China arguments from the advocacy tone guide.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "field_id": "microsoft_forms:01:r31cbfcb499de4595bed5eb904553c33c:afa68d39d991",
            "label": "Does this Project have Ties to Nebraska's First Congressional District? Why is this Request Important to NE-01? ",
            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* The Board of Regents of the University of Nebraska in Lincoln has received over $1.7 million in grants for research tied to NASA Science missions.\n* District researchers use NASA data to improve drought tracking and irrigation scheduling, providing direct economic benefits to Nebraska farmers.\n* Local technology companies such as Li-Cor, Inc. and Metgreen Solutions contribute specialized equipment and services to the NASA supply chain.",
            "rationale": "Cites specific local grant and contract recipients from the NASA spending context for NE-1.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "field_id": "microsoft_forms:01:r63ed94098f984794bc879d97cfccb710:6e033dfc20be",
            "label": "Additional Comments:",
            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": false,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* Space science remains a top-performing federal activity in public polling and enjoys broad, non-partisan support.\n* Consistent funding ensures the U.S. continues to set the norms for space exploration in the 21st century.",
            "rationale": "Includes references to public polling and international norm-setting from the talking points.",
            "confidence": "high"
          }
        ]
